  "doc_id": "31969",
  "text": "Cyto-ID, a recently developed cationic amphilic tracer dye, labels autophagic compartments with minimal staining of lysosomes, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] suggesting that it is a specific autophagy marker. Here we took advantage of this fluorescent dye and developed a Cyto-ID-based fluorescence spectrophotometric assay (abbreviated as the Cyto-ID assay) that permits high content performance and measures the size of autophagic compartments which makes it possible to monitor autophagy flux. Compared to other traditional autophagydetecting approaches, this assay is considerably more sensitive, reliable, and timesaving thereby providing a platform for drug screening and has a potential clinical application as a diagnostic tool to gauge autophagy responses in patients.",
